variable.name: PLATE_ID
variable.comment: Character field Blank = Field not filled in. Non-blank = Field filled in.

variable.name: ENKUR_I
variable.value: Set to missing because CV was above allowable limit

variable.name: UCMGP_I
variable.description: Indicator variable for Uncarboxylated matrix gla protein
variable.value: Set to missing because CV was above allowable limit

variable.name: IDTYPE
variable.comment: IDTYPE and ID taken together form a unique study participant identification number.

variable.name: ENKUR
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for ENKUR is 3.31E+03 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 8.65E+05 pg/mL. ENKUR values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use ENKUR_I to see what records are below and above these limits. There were no outlier cutoffs for ENKUR.

variable.name: ENKUR_CV
variable.comment: There were no outlier cutoffs for ENKUR.

variable.name: UCMGP
variable.description: Uncarboxylated matrix gla protein (sample type: plasma)
variable.comment: The lower detectable limit for UCMGP is 9.11+03 pg/mL and the upper detectable limit is 2.06E+06 pg/mL. UCMGP values below or above these limits were set to the lower or upper detectable limit respectively. Use UCMGP_I to see what records are below and above these limits. UCMGP values were set to unknown if UCMGP_CV was greater than or equal to 40.3 for Offspring (IDTYPE = 1) or 58.2 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3).

variable.name: UCMGP_CV
variable.description: CV for Uncarboxylated matrix gla protein
variable.comment: UCMGP values were set to unknown if UCMGP_CV was greater than or equal to 40.3 for Offspring (IDTYPE = 1) or 58.2 for Gen 3 (IDTYPE = 3).

variable.name: RUN_DATE
variable.comment: Date includes month, day and year, however, coding manual displays only month and year to preserve confidentiality.
